Hi Michael...

Check out Ken Yap's links at
http://www.geocities.com/SiliconValley/lab/9247/
I think the kits that Ken has are very early and oriented toward MVS.

Also, look at Martin Richards' links at http://www.cl.cam.ac.uk/users/mr/
He has a much-updated BCPL compiler, ready-to-run under Linux..

I've not seen a BCPL prepared just for TOPS-10, but I'll bet someone
has done the bootstrap at some time or another..

